05"}, {"t": "New York, New York: New York, New York", "c": "John Kander", "w": "36120"}]}, {"id": "5562", "date": "1987-09-10", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41989", "date": "1987-09-11", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41990", "date": "1987-09-12", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41991", "date": "1987-09-15", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41992", "date": "1987-09-16", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41993", "date": "1987-09-17", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "353", "date": "1988-05-11", "label": "Irving Berlin 100th Birthday Celebration", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Always", "c": "Irving Berlin", "w": "39399"}, {"t": "When I Lost You", "c": "Irving Berlin", "w": "108559"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Sheila Jordan", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "The interviewee mentions Frank Sinatra only in the context of the interviewer's prompt ('You've mentioned all the personnel...'). The interviewee's response discusses Charlie Parker, Dizzy Gillespie, Frank Foster, and others, but never mentions Frank Sinatra or describes any personal interaction wit", "doc_title": "Sheila Jordan — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Jordan-Sheila/Jordan_Sheila_Interview_Transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Tom Malone", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I got the job with Frank by playing the tuba over the telephone... Frank called to say I had the job playing bass with him. The next day, after I left, he calls to say I had the job playing with George Duke and Jean Luc Ponty on the tour in ’73.", "doc_title": "Tom Malone interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, May 3, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/tom-malone-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-may-3-2023"}, {"speaker": "Michael Moore", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "You turn on the radio, or put on a Frank Sinatra record, and play along with it... I think that if Frank Sinatra were starting out singing now, he’d have a hell of a time getting a job", "doc_title": "Michael Moore interviewed by Monk Rowe, Chautauqua, New York, September 12, 1997", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/michael-moore-interviewed-monk-rowe-chautauqua-new-york-september-12-1997"}, {"speaker": "Bernie Kirsh", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Frank Sinatra is mentioned by the interviewer as part of a playlist of top songs from 1966; the interviewee does not mention any personal interaction or relationship with Sinatra.", "doc_title": "Bernie Kirsh interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, August 27, 2022", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/bernie-kirsh-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-august-27-2022"}, {"speaker": "Jack Palmer", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Frank Sinatra joined us in May... Frank joined us and Harry introduced him there... Yeah, in Harry’s band... So Frank says, 'Well can I room with you?' I says, 'Yeah, okay.'", "doc_title": "Jack Palmer interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clinton, New York, September 24, 1997", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/jack-palmer-interviewed-monk-rowe-clinton-new-york-september-24-1997"}, {"speaker": "Harry Edison", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "we went on tour with Sinatra, a lot of times... I still record with him... I played with him six years... Made all the recordings with him", "doc_title": "68427_Harry Edison oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68427/"}]}